{
  "texts": [
    "From Table 7 we can draw into the following conclusions: 1) The results of \"Cooccurrence number\" show that the landmark cooccurrence priors greatly facilitate the landmark discovery, e.g., \"num=5\" outperforms \"num=0\" by 0.55% and 0.64% in SR and SPL, respectively.",
    "Moreover, the results of \"num=5,10\".14 76.25 65.15 60.08 52.69 50.07 54.25 34.40 34.05 23.33 55.13 59.60 37.13 33.18 22.25 46.34 42.92 60.85 57.11 38.85show that adding too many co-occurrences may not bring further performance improvement.",
    "It is reasonable since too many co-occurrences may introduce unexpected noise to mislead the agent in the meanwhile.",
    "2) The results of \"Landmark Shifting\" show that landmark shifting module is helpful for accurate landmark discovery.",
    "Especially, \"Shift\" outperforms \"Global\" by 0.91% in SPL.3) The results of \"strategies for fusing the corrected landmark features and the original observation features\" show that \"summation\" outperforms \"concatenation\" and \"concatenation\" is comparable with the baseline."
  ]
}